  "summary": [
    "This room knows more than it acts on. Across 64 responses, the average sensing score sits at 5.6 out of 7 \u2014 a confident read of the competitive landscape. But signal-to-action velocity lands at 2.4. That is a gap of 3.3 points. The radar is on. It is not connected to the cockpit.",
    "Spotting external opportunities averages 5.5. Detecting fundamental shifts averages 5.5. Competitive anticipation averages 5.8. These are not low scores. This room rates its sensing capability with real confidence.",
    "Then velocity drops the floor out. At 2.4, Poll 6 is the lowest-scoring item by a wide margin. 62 out of 64 respondents (97%) land in the Stuck-at-Sensing quadrant \u2014 high awareness, low action. Only 1 qualify as Leaders who both sense and act above the midpoint. This is not a detection problem. It is a conversion problem.",
    "The gap is remarkably consistent across segments. Company size does not save you \u2014 the spread across size bands is just 0.4 points. More resources did not produce faster action. Seniority does not save you either \u2014 VPs and managers report essentially the same bottleneck. Whatever is blocking the path from signal to decision, it is structural, not hierarchical.",
    "The fix is not more intelligence. It is a shorter distance from signal to decision. Every organisation in this room has built the sensing muscle. The masterclass question is whether you will build the acting muscle to match it."
